### Area

ldap

### Describe the bug

Hello everyone,

we are enforcing authentication with Kerberos. Usernames consist of surname and first name like this:

DoeJ@LOCALDOMAIN.COM

"Kerberos principal attribute" is set to userPrincipalName in LDAP config.

We are experiencing an issue whenever an employee changes it's name (marriage!). Keycloak updates all attributes including the profile name except KERBEROS_PRINCIPAL, thus the user cannot log in anymore.

This issue was already present in Keycloak 24.x

Log output:

```
Debug is  true storeKey true useTicketCache false useKeyTab false doNotPrompt false ticketCache is null isInitiator true KeyTab is null refreshKrb5Config is false principal is null tryFirstPass is false useFirstPass is false storePass is false clearPass is false
		[Krb5LoginModule] user entered username: doej@LOCALDOMAIN.COM
		[Krb5LoginModule] authentication failed
Client not found in Kerberos database (6)
```




### Version

25.0.2

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

KERBEROS_PRINCIPAL should update/sync according to LDAP data.

### Actual behavior

Username and Attributes updates execpt KERBEROS_PRINCIPAL on full and partial user sync.

### How to Reproduce?

- Setup Keycloak with LDAP & Kerberos Authentication.
- Use LDAP-federation with Kerberos configuration
- Import User from LDAP with "Kerberos principal attribute" set to userPrincipalName
- Change UserPrincipalName/Username in LDAP.
- Try full-sync / partial-sync.
- Go to Users -> User Profile
- KERBEROS_PRINCIPAL is not updated

